page.title: 15Houses of Coatham High St.
page.content: On High Street West there was once a school but now it is a Training- Centre. Most of the houses in High Street West are terraced houses. The reasons that most of them are terraced are that they save space and they are cheaper to build. The oldest houses in High Sreet West are the ones that are facing the sea. The oldest house in High Street West is the Yeoman's House. It was built in 1698. Above the door are the initials of the first people who owned it. The initials are G and I. On the north side of High Street West there are a lot of semi-detached houses which were not built until the 1930's. Next to these are some detached houses built much later in the 1960's. The rest of the north side is made up of terraces, also built about the 1930s, which includes The Cleveland Public House.
